{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"23a97d8b-e922-47ec-9f5b-209925dcef0d","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Single-org Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain contoso.onmicrosoft.com --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C --domain contoso.b2c.login --client-id <id>\n```\n\nFor JWT Bearer auth without Azure AD, use `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually. Would you like help scaffolding a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8ce318d7-ef8f-4932-ac1e-ed444a3a4588","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/development question rather than something specific to the codebase. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nThey're asking about:\n1. What template to use for a web API project with authentication\n2. What authentication options are available\n\nThis is a general knowledge question - I don't need to search the codebase for this. I'll provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":369,"requestId":"93C7:1ED665:A38D9E:BCD580:69F2A76F"},"id":"6d625708-8436-4c08-a564-15e35cb454a7","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:51:04.290Z","parentId":"400ca0f7-a955-4e0d-a1e3-3b54496fc3f5"}
